name: AnyInfectionICD10CM
title: Any Infection ICD10CM
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values identifies patients who have a diagnosis of an infection.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients who have a diagnosis of an infection.  Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element will map to the Diagnosis category.),(Inclusion Criteria: Only use codes which represent a diagnosis of infection as defined by the measure steward.  Codes used are to be ICD10CM codes only.),(Exclusion Criteria: These include codes for fungal infections, viral infections and infections that are not documented as current or active.)
